                                p.recipie-subTitle.mb-1 You mean with the pods?
                                p.recipie-ingredient.pt-2.mb-0  Fava Bean season in Lebanon means sitting on a terrace with the warm sun hitting after a long winter, holding beer bottles before a big Sunday meal. 
                                p.recipie-ingredient.pt-2.mb-0  But before splitting beans and pods, when favas are still green and tender, this old recipe is made to savor the whole flavor of the pods.
                            .col-12.p-0.m-0.pt-2
                                p.recipie-subTitle.mb-1 Method
                                p.recipie-ingredient.pt-2.mb-0  Wash the fava bean pods thoroughly. Cut the pods into two-inch bites.  Meanwhile, fry the onions with some olive oil. 
                                p.recipie-ingredient.pt-2.mb-0  When they are cooked and golden, pour the beans into the pot, and toss regularly. 
                                p.recipie-ingredient.pt-2.mb-0  Wash the Coriander. In a food processor mince the garlic, coriander and salt until they are very fine. Pour the lemon juice over them. 
                                p.recipie-ingredient.pt-2.mb-0  When the fava beans are tender and have lost their bitterness, add to the pot the coriander mixture and stir. Salt to taste. Simmer with the lid open for 7-10 mins and serve.
